<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb8cb7763-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s471"><num value="471">§ 471.</num><heading> Obligations or securities of United States</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Whoever, with intent to defraud, falsely makes, forges, counterfeits, or alters any obligation or other security of the United States, shall be fined under this title or imprisoned not more than 20 years, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb8cb7764-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645">June 25, 1948, ch. 645</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/705">62 Stat. 705</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tXXXIII/s330016/1/K">Pub. L. 103–322, title XXXIII, § 330016(1)(K)</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2147">108 Stat. 2147</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/107/56/tIII/s374/b">Pub. L. 107–56, title III, § 374(b)</ref>, <date date="2001-10-26">Oct. 26, 2001</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/115/340">115 Stat. 340</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb8cb7765-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idb8cb7766-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 18, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 262 (<ref href="/us/act/1909-03-04/ch321/s148">Mar. 4, 1909, ch. 321, § 148</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/35/1115">35 Stat. 1115</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Mandatory punishment provision was rephrased in the alternative.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes in phraseology were made.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb8cb7767-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idb8cb7768-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2001—<ref href="/us/pl/107/56">Pub. L. 107–56</ref> substituted “20 years” for “fifteen years”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1994—<ref href="/us/pl/103/322">Pub. L. 103–322</ref> substituted “fined under this title” for “fined not more than $5,000”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
